.TH DBX-ANALYZE 1 "2026-05-27" "dbx 0.20.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-analyze \- interactively pick tables to exclude from backups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx analyze
.I host
.I database
.PP
.B dbx stats
.I host
.I database
.SH DESCRIPTION
Show a sorted table-stats view (rows, on-disk MB) for
.IR host / database
and let the user toggle tables to exclude from data dumps. The
selection is written back to
.IR config.json
under
.IR .hosts[host].databases[database].exclude_data .
.PP
Pre-existing exclusions are shown pre-selected; deselect a table to
re-include it. Schema is always dumped \(em the exclusion only affects
table data.
.PP
Requires
.B fzf
for the interactive picker. Without
.BR fzf ,
falls back to a sorted plain-text report.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
dbx analyze production b2c
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dbx/config.json
Exclusion list is persisted under
.IR .hosts[host].databases[database].exclude_data .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-backup (1),
.BR fzf (1).
